Police have concluded the screening of 4,438 Kaduna State indigenes aspiring to become police constables. Police  Successful ones would write a Computer-Based Test at a date to be announced later, Jalige told the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Kaduna on Sunday. He said applicants indicated interests in the job from the 23 local government areas of the state and that the screening was held between Feb. 1 and Feb. 20 at the Police College, Kaduna. 